    "bio": "I am an Assistant Professor in the Department of Linguistics at Boston University. I received my PhD from Harvard University in 2023, working with Jesse Snedeker, and completed a postdoctoral fellowship at Tufts University. I use psycholinguistic methods \u2014 including neuroimaging, eye-tracking, and computational modeling \u2014 to better understand how language develops, functions, and adapts in complex, real-world environments. In the Duckling Lab, we ask how children learn the language(s) around them: how and when do we acquire linguistic forms and their meanings? We also study what makes language easier or harder to understand and produce across various populations and ages.",
